WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:03.337
-I'm Letty.
-Javier.

00:03.371 --> 00:05.005
[ Gun cocks ]

00:05.039 --> 00:07.741
You're not an English teacher.
You're a thief.

00:07.775 --> 00:10.678
Amazing, considering
what you do for a living.

00:10.711 --> 00:11.745
[ Gunshot ]

00:11.779 --> 00:15.015
And if you don't tell the truth,
Silk will!

00:15.049 --> 00:17.585
When I was young watching
movies, I always thought

00:17.618 --> 00:20.354
it was so stupid when
they dump a body in the river.

00:20.388 --> 00:21.889
I thought, why don't
they make a friend

00:21.922 --> 00:24.258
at a funeral home
and cremate the body?

00:24.292 --> 00:27.095
-Your sister lives here?
-She used to.

00:27.128 --> 00:28.329
Thanks for doing this.

00:28.362 --> 00:29.697
I'm driving down
to Ava's anyway.

00:29.730 --> 00:30.731
That was a huge help.

00:30.764 --> 00:31.799
Hey, Uncle Jav.

00:38.806 --> 00:40.708
-Jacob.
-Hi, Dad.

00:40.741 --> 00:42.876
Get out! Get out of here!
I will get my son.

00:42.910 --> 00:45.045
Don't worry, custody almost
always goes to the mother.

00:45.079 --> 00:46.114
Unless the mother is me.

00:46.147 --> 00:48.082
Rhonda Lashever, FBI.

00:48.116 --> 00:51.552
Lashever:
Your former parole officer
said that you might be willing

00:51.585 --> 00:53.254
to help me locate this man.

00:53.287 --> 00:55.523
They will guarantee
you get custody of Jacob.

00:55.556 --> 00:58.292
All you have to do
is give us his handle.

00:58.326 --> 00:59.793
This is you?
Yeah.

00:59.827 --> 01:01.695
Philanthropist?

01:01.729 --> 01:08.769
**

01:08.802 --> 01:10.971
I do hereby grant
full custody

01:11.004 --> 01:14.142
of Jacob Michael Raines
to his mother.

01:14.175 --> 01:16.410
I sold you out to the FBI.

01:16.444 --> 01:17.978
How else do you think
I got Jacob?

01:18.011 --> 01:20.581
If you don't want to be with me,
that's fine, but please,

01:20.614 --> 01:23.151
don't walk in there
and throw your life away.

01:23.184 --> 01:27.988
If you're gonna raise a kid,
you have to be totally selfless,

01:28.021 --> 01:31.459
and that will be a good thing
for you to try on.

01:31.492 --> 01:33.093
I was so hoping
you'd be here.

01:33.127 --> 01:34.395
I'm here.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.663
We need to go right now.

01:35.696 --> 01:37.631
Oh, shit.

01:37.665 --> 01:39.167
He got away.

01:39.200 --> 01:40.834
We'll find him.

01:45.005 --> 01:47.341
* Ba ba ba ba ba ba ba

01:47.375 --> 01:49.343
* I trust my heart to you

01:49.377 --> 01:51.445
* Every word I say is true

01:51.479 --> 01:52.746
[ Moaning ]

01:52.780 --> 01:54.182
* I've been
on my good behavior *

01:54.215 --> 01:56.184
[ Cellphone rings ]

01:56.217 --> 02:00.188
-Oh, my God.
-* Darling, why you run away

02:00.221 --> 02:02.190
[ Ringing continues ]

02:02.223 --> 02:05.959
[ Panting, moaning ]

02:05.993 --> 02:09.830
[ Ringing continues ]

02:12.833 --> 02:15.869
Why'd you set
the alarm so early?

02:15.903 --> 02:18.539
I thought you were
working the lunch shift.

02:18.572 --> 02:19.840
I am.

02:19.873 --> 02:22.276
But you're taking Jacob
to sign up for school.

02:22.310 --> 02:25.112
[ Ringing continues ]

02:25.145 --> 02:26.647
Oh.

02:26.680 --> 02:29.183
Yeah.

02:29.217 --> 02:30.284
Yeah.

02:30.318 --> 02:33.654
Jacob: Are you guys done?

02:33.687 --> 02:35.823
[ Ringing continues ]

02:35.856 --> 02:36.890
[ Sighs ]

02:36.924 --> 02:38.226
[ School bell rings ]

02:38.259 --> 02:39.627
How can I help you?

02:39.660 --> 02:42.129
I'd love for my son
to go to school here.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.397
Okay, where is he?

02:43.431 --> 02:46.367
Right there.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.669
All right,
fill this out.

02:48.702 --> 02:51.672
All 17 pages,
plus the birth certificate,

02:51.705 --> 02:54.074
record of immunization,
former school records,

02:54.107 --> 02:55.576
and proof of guardianship.

02:55.609 --> 02:56.910
Of what?

02:56.944 --> 02:58.412
Guardianship, custody.

02:58.446 --> 03:00.481
Why would I pay a ton of money
for him to go to private school

03:00.514 --> 03:02.049
if he wasn't actually my kid?

03:02.082 --> 03:03.317
We need the records.

03:03.351 --> 03:05.886
Look, we just moved here
a few days ago.

03:05.919 --> 03:07.588
We're living
only a few blocks away,

03:07.621 --> 03:09.089
and he really needs
to be in school.

03:09.122 --> 03:11.259
If you could just start now,
I promise I'll get you

03:11.292 --> 03:12.926
all the forms and records
A.S.A.P.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.262
If he could
just start now?

03:14.295 --> 03:15.729
Yeah.

03:15.763 --> 03:17.265
I'm sorry, it's the middle
of the school year.

03:17.298 --> 03:19.767
We have no room
for your son.

03:19.800 --> 03:22.102
For anyone, or for
my son specifically?

03:22.135 --> 03:23.704
For anyone.

03:23.737 --> 03:25.706
Okay, you know when
they say there are

03:25.739 --> 03:27.741
no more tables available
at a restaurant,

03:27.775 --> 03:29.543
and there's always
one open in the back?

03:29.577 --> 03:32.780
There are no more
tables available.

03:32.813 --> 03:39.019
**

03:39.052 --> 03:45.192
**

03:45.225 --> 03:46.694
All right.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.862
Fill out the forms,
and if any other student

03:48.896 --> 03:51.632
moves or drops out or flunks,

03:51.665 --> 03:53.701
your son will be third
on the wait list.

03:53.734 --> 03:55.269
Third?

03:55.303 --> 03:57.971
I'm sure he'll be in
by April or May.

03:58.005 --> 03:58.972
Seriously?

03:59.006 --> 04:02.643
As long as he nails
the interview.

04:02.676 --> 04:06.079
This isn't
how a bribe works.

04:06.113 --> 04:07.415
We'll home school you.

04:07.448 --> 04:08.816
What?
It's a thing.

04:08.849 --> 04:11.218
I know what it is.
We're not doing that.

04:11.251 --> 04:13.821
Yes, we are, and you don't
get to talk to me that way.

04:13.854 --> 04:15.956
You never even graduated
from high school,

04:15.989 --> 04:18.058
and Javier doesn't
speak English.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.327
Yes, he does.

04:19.360 --> 04:20.728
You know what I mean.

04:20.761 --> 04:21.795
Right.

04:21.829 --> 04:24.432
But home schooling will be
way more fun.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.934
We can learn about whatever
we want whenever we want.

04:26.967 --> 04:29.403
That's the exact opposite
point of school.

04:29.437 --> 04:30.838
Says who?

04:30.871 --> 04:38.011
**

04:38.045 --> 04:45.118
**

04:45.152 --> 04:48.356
[ Ammunition clip clicks ]

04:48.389 --> 04:51.158
**

04:51.191 --> 04:53.026
Can't I just go to
a normal public school?

04:53.060 --> 04:54.362
They would have to
let me in.

04:54.395 --> 04:56.029
No, they wouldn't.

04:56.063 --> 04:58.666
We've been here three days,
and we're renting an Airbnb.

04:58.699 --> 04:59.833
You need
a permanent address.

04:59.867 --> 05:01.702
So, let's get
a permanent address.

05:01.735 --> 05:03.371
We need to be sure
we like it here.

05:03.404 --> 05:04.505
I like it here.

05:04.538 --> 05:06.206
And we need enough money.

05:06.239 --> 05:08.442
Can't you just steal some?

05:08.476 --> 05:12.380
Baby, listen to me,
I'm not --

05:12.413 --> 05:14.682
I'm not doing
those things anymore.

05:14.715 --> 05:17.451
You are all I want in this
world, and now that I have you,

05:17.485 --> 05:20.454
I'm gonna do everything I can
to make a normal life for us.

05:20.488 --> 05:22.990
So why are we using
fake names?

05:23.023 --> 05:25.058
Um...

05:25.092 --> 05:27.828
All the things I used to do are
why they took you away from me.

05:27.861 --> 05:30.063
You know that, right?
Yeah.

05:30.097 --> 05:33.033
Well, so, there are
people from my past

05:33.066 --> 05:37.371
who might try and find me,
and I don't want that to happen.

05:37.405 --> 05:38.639
I want a clean start.

05:38.672 --> 05:41.475
If we use new names,
we can easily do that.

05:41.509 --> 05:44.812
Does that make sense?

05:44.845 --> 05:48.582
We will have a real house,
you will go to a real school,

05:48.616 --> 05:53.020
we will have a normal life,
do you hear me?

05:53.053 --> 05:57.858
[ Horn blows ]

05:57.891 --> 06:03.096
[ Fishing reel clicking ]

06:03.130 --> 06:07.635
[ Seagulls crying ]

06:12.973 --> 06:15.543
Beautiful day.

06:15.576 --> 06:18.278
It's supposed to be
like this tomorrow, too.

06:18.311 --> 06:20.781
Good.

06:20.814 --> 06:23.884
But I don't think you
will be here tomorrow.

06:23.917 --> 06:25.919
Why not?

06:25.953 --> 06:29.857
I know what you did to your
brother a few years ago.

06:29.890 --> 06:32.860
He wants you
to pay for that.

06:32.893 --> 06:38.231
He asked me if I could help him,
and I said that I would.

06:38.265 --> 06:40.434
Funny.

06:40.468 --> 06:43.103
I got the same story
about you.

06:43.136 --> 06:45.238
Only I was told
to shoot you.

06:45.272 --> 06:46.740
[ Gunshot ]

06:46.774 --> 06:50.210
[ Grunting ]

06:50.243 --> 06:52.145
[ Grunts ]

06:52.179 --> 06:56.149
[ Grunting ]

06:56.183 --> 06:57.618
**

06:57.651 --> 06:59.987
Aah!

07:00.020 --> 07:03.223
[ Grunting ]

07:03.256 --> 07:08.496
**

07:08.529 --> 07:14.468
[ Groans ]

07:14.502 --> 07:23.143
**

07:23.176 --> 07:26.013
[ Gunshot ]

07:26.046 --> 07:29.182
**

07:29.216 --> 07:31.519
Does my name
have to be Michael, though?

07:31.552 --> 07:33.020
Your middle name
is Michael.

07:33.053 --> 07:34.922
But if I get to have
a whole, new name,

07:34.955 --> 07:37.357
why can't it be more
interesting, like Tristan?

07:37.390 --> 07:39.827
Tristan? No.

07:39.860 --> 07:41.929
People named Tristan
are fictional characters

07:41.962 --> 07:43.764
who have to turn into animals
so that women will

07:43.797 --> 07:45.198
have sex with them.

07:45.232 --> 07:47.167
Fine. Then Lachlan.

07:47.200 --> 07:48.702
It's Scottish.

07:48.736 --> 07:50.671
Exactly.
You can't be Scottish.

07:50.704 --> 07:52.439
I could be half-Scottish.

07:52.472 --> 07:54.141
No, it's -- it's a thinker.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.208
A what?

07:55.242 --> 07:56.677
People will think
too much about it.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.045
You never want people
to think too much.

07:58.078 --> 08:00.814
Just be Michael. Trust me.
This is what I'm good at.

08:00.848 --> 08:02.115
Can we just tell
the public school

08:02.149 --> 08:03.617
this is
our permanent address?

08:03.651 --> 08:05.953
They'll know it's not true
in two seconds.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.788
Don't worry,
I'm gonna get everything we need

08:07.821 --> 08:09.823
for home school.

08:09.857 --> 08:11.458
How will you know
what to get?

08:11.491 --> 08:12.560
What do you mean?

08:12.593 --> 08:13.894
You're not a teacher.

08:13.927 --> 08:15.563
I remember sixth grade.

08:15.596 --> 08:17.130
I'll be back soon.
Just hang here.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.800
-And do what?
-I don't know.

08:19.833 --> 08:22.603
It's recess.
Play.

08:24.738 --> 08:28.576
[ Horn blows ]

08:28.609 --> 08:31.712
[ Birds cawing ]

08:31.745 --> 08:38.085
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

08:38.118 --> 08:40.153
Hi.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.422
Where are you?

08:42.455 --> 08:43.757
Working.

08:43.791 --> 08:46.193
They called me in early.

08:46.226 --> 08:48.495
Oh. Okay.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.763
Bye.

08:49.797 --> 08:52.432
* Hard time forgiving

08:52.465 --> 08:55.035
* Even harder forgetting

08:55.068 --> 08:57.204
* Before you do something

08:57.237 --> 08:59.773
* You might regret, friend

08:59.807 --> 09:02.610
* Bricks are caving in

09:02.643 --> 09:04.778
* Oh, how sweet this sin

09:04.812 --> 09:07.615
* I left you the keys

09:07.648 --> 09:09.783
* You won't let me in

09:09.817 --> 09:12.219
* Hard time forgiving

09:12.252 --> 09:14.955
* Even harder forgetting

09:14.988 --> 09:17.257
* Before you do something

09:17.290 --> 09:20.794
* You might regret, friend

09:20.828 --> 09:24.264
[ Plastic rustling ]

09:24.297 --> 09:34.274
**

09:34.307 --> 09:36.744
Oh.

09:36.777 --> 09:39.880
* If I'm a good lover
after the rush *

09:39.913 --> 09:42.049
* If I'm still around to love

09:42.082 --> 09:44.117
* What if I'm still
looking for that love *

09:44.151 --> 09:45.886
Female voice:
Your call has been forwarded

09:45.919 --> 09:47.154
to an automated
voice message system.

09:47.187 --> 09:48.588
* I can see right through you

09:48.622 --> 09:50.290
* And there's nothing
on the other side *

09:50.323 --> 09:52.092
* I fight with these
thoughts every night *

09:52.125 --> 09:56.764
* If I'm still a good lover
after the rush *

09:56.797 --> 09:59.332
* Laws, trouble,
can't get home *

09:59.366 --> 10:01.769
* I'm just a girl
with a microphone *

10:01.802 --> 10:04.304
* Moon chasing,
satellite racing *

10:04.337 --> 10:06.807
* Show me those electric bones

10:06.840 --> 10:09.276
* Moon chasing,
satellite racing *

10:09.309 --> 10:11.611
* Show me those electric bones

10:11.645 --> 10:13.246
* And I can't swim,
but I'm not sinking *

10:13.280 --> 10:14.915
Can I help you
find anything?

10:14.948 --> 10:17.150
Do you have these in a 10?
I don't see any in the pile.

10:17.184 --> 10:19.186
I'm sure we do,
let me check in the back.

10:19.219 --> 10:20.120
Thanks, Meg.

10:20.153 --> 10:22.455
* Show me those electric bones

10:22.489 --> 10:26.960
**

10:26.994 --> 10:29.496
* Laws, trouble,
can't get home *

10:29.529 --> 10:32.165
* I'm just a girl
with a microphone *

10:32.199 --> 10:34.434
* Laws, trouble,
can't get home *

10:34.467 --> 10:37.437
* I'm just a girl
with a microphone *

10:37.470 --> 10:39.639
-You're late.
-I know, I'm sorry.

10:39.673 --> 10:42.275
My kid was sick.

10:42.309 --> 10:45.979
**

10:46.013 --> 10:50.283
[ Garage door opens ]

10:50.317 --> 11:00.060
**

11:00.093 --> 11:03.864
[ Garage door closes ]

11:03.897 --> 11:12.539
**

11:12.572 --> 11:20.981
**

11:21.014 --> 11:24.952
[ Garage door opens ]

11:37.898 --> 11:40.267
-Hey.
-Hi.

11:40.300 --> 11:42.602
-What are you doing in here?
-What are you doing in here?

11:42.635 --> 11:44.504
[ Chuckles ]
I asked you first.

11:44.537 --> 11:46.439
You never park in here.

11:46.473 --> 11:47.674
It's supposed to rain.

11:47.707 --> 11:48.942
No, it's not.

11:48.976 --> 11:50.343
What are you doing here?

11:50.377 --> 11:52.746
I was looking
for a glue gun.

11:52.780 --> 11:54.681
A what?

11:54.714 --> 11:58.618
Excuse me.

11:58.651 --> 12:01.621
Is this your son?

12:01.654 --> 12:03.056
Are you okay, baby?

12:03.090 --> 12:04.792
Jacob: Yeah, I was just playing
at the beach.

12:04.825 --> 12:07.027
Is there a problem,
Officer?

12:07.060 --> 12:08.461
Are you his father?

12:08.495 --> 12:11.799
No, but I'm his mother.

12:11.832 --> 12:13.300
Where's his father?

12:13.333 --> 12:14.701
Myrtle Beach.

12:14.734 --> 12:15.969
Why? Who cares?

12:16.003 --> 12:17.404
I found him alone
at the beach.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.807
I played outside all the time
when I was a kid.

12:19.840 --> 12:21.308
Things are
different now.

12:21.341 --> 12:24.711
Children can't be alone
in public places.

12:24.744 --> 12:27.080
We're very sorry,
Officer.

12:27.114 --> 12:29.416
Thank you for
bringing him home.

12:29.449 --> 12:31.785
What is the law,
so we know for next time?

12:31.819 --> 12:34.254
-Who are you?
-There's no law.

12:34.287 --> 12:36.489
The only thing in
the state of Georgia is that

12:36.523 --> 12:39.726
children under 8 years old
shouldn't be left alone at home.

12:39.759 --> 12:42.395
Keep reading that thing.

12:42.429 --> 12:45.665
Children between
the ages of 9 and 12,

12:45.698 --> 12:48.836
based on level of maturity,
can be left home alone

12:48.869 --> 12:53.340
for brief periods of time.

12:53.373 --> 12:54.942
He's very mature.

12:58.879 --> 13:00.447
If you say so.

13:00.480 --> 13:02.682
I do.

13:02.715 --> 13:04.251
Thank you, Officer.

13:04.284 --> 13:05.819
Let's go

13:05.853 --> 13:09.189
[ Birds chirping ]

13:09.222 --> 13:11.524
I told you to stay here.

13:11.558 --> 13:13.861
You can't go out and do
whatever you want by yourself.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.762
You just told the cop
that I could.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.330
Yes, to get him to go away,

13:17.364 --> 13:19.266
but you can't wander off
without telling me.

13:19.299 --> 13:21.334
I'm supposed to stay
inside all the time?

13:21.368 --> 13:23.770
Yes, that's
what Wi-Fi is for.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.373
Why were you at the beach?
Oh, wait, let me guess.

13:26.406 --> 13:27.875
You were staring
at the water,

13:27.908 --> 13:29.376
thinking about how much
you hate me.

13:29.409 --> 13:30.310
At first.

13:30.343 --> 13:31.845
Because of
the school thing.

13:31.879 --> 13:33.213
W-what happened?

13:33.246 --> 13:35.315
The private school thing,
it's not gonna work.

13:35.348 --> 13:37.117
We'll have to home school
him for now.

13:37.150 --> 13:38.218
What's a home school?

13:38.251 --> 13:39.819
Exactly what it sounds like.

13:39.853 --> 13:41.288
It doesn't sound good.

13:41.321 --> 13:44.624
-Apple wants to help.
-Apple?

13:44.657 --> 13:45.893
Is that a person?

13:45.926 --> 13:47.895
I think he means
the computers.

13:47.928 --> 13:50.130
She's a person.
She's my age.

13:50.163 --> 13:51.464
I met her just now
at the beach.

13:51.498 --> 13:53.833
She lives right on the water
in a huge house.

13:53.867 --> 13:57.204
She likes me because I'm black.

13:57.237 --> 13:59.006
She wants me to go
to her school.

13:59.039 --> 14:00.473
A different school
from this morning.

14:00.507 --> 14:03.010
What does that have to do
with you being black?

14:03.043 --> 14:04.644
She's running
for class president,

14:04.677 --> 14:07.414
and diversity is part of her
campaign platform or something.

14:07.447 --> 14:09.349
Anyway, then her mom
came out of their house

14:09.382 --> 14:11.418
and asked who I was
and who my parents are.

14:11.451 --> 14:13.420
Because you're black.
Probably.

14:13.453 --> 14:15.088
I told her that you
weren't black, though,

14:15.122 --> 14:16.523
and I think she felt better.

14:16.556 --> 14:18.391
You don't need to tell
people anything.

14:18.425 --> 14:21.361
I know. I didn't.
But I told her that you would.

14:21.394 --> 14:23.096
They're coming over at 5:00.

14:23.130 --> 14:24.497
I'm sorry, what?

14:24.531 --> 14:27.267
I invited them because
Apple thinks maybe her mom

14:27.300 --> 14:28.936
can help me get into
that school.

14:28.969 --> 14:30.337
-Jacob!
-What?

14:30.370 --> 14:31.604
It's just her and her mom.

14:31.638 --> 14:33.040
Her dad's working late.

14:33.073 --> 14:35.408
You can't just invite
strangers into our house.

14:35.442 --> 14:38.078
They're not strangers.
They're neighbors.

14:38.111 --> 14:40.113
Javier can make food.

14:40.147 --> 14:42.282
Tonight is not
the best for me.

14:42.315 --> 14:43.951
Me neither.
We'll do it another night.

14:43.984 --> 14:46.619
No, we won't. I want to go to
a real school with other kids.

14:46.653 --> 14:50.190
You said we would
have a normal life.

14:50.223 --> 14:53.526
I know.
I know I did. I'm sorry.

14:53.560 --> 14:55.028
I'm trying.

14:55.062 --> 14:58.665
I -- I got you some
new clothes today.

15:00.467 --> 15:02.135
Okay, you know what?
It's fine.

15:02.169 --> 15:05.105
We'll --
we'll have them over.

15:05.138 --> 15:07.740
We have a chicken
I can cook.

15:07.774 --> 15:09.109
You can help.

15:09.142 --> 15:13.113
Go try your new clothes
first.

15:13.146 --> 15:14.414
We are not
ready for this.

15:14.447 --> 15:15.815
This is what
you're good at.

15:15.848 --> 15:18.318
Being a mother?
No, not a good one, not yet.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.820
Especially not one who
talks to other mothers.

15:20.853 --> 15:22.822
You can pretend.
No, I can't.

15:22.855 --> 15:24.457
If I could pretend
at being a good mother,

15:24.491 --> 15:26.059
they would never have taken
Jacob away from me

15:26.093 --> 15:27.227
in the first place.

15:27.260 --> 15:28.828
[ Sighs ]

15:28.861 --> 15:31.831
Letty.

15:31.864 --> 15:34.634
This is what you wanted.

15:34.667 --> 15:44.477
**

15:46.513 --> 15:56.489
**

15:56.523 --> 15:58.425
[ Sighs ]

15:58.458 --> 16:00.727
[ Door opens ]

16:04.331 --> 16:06.599
You look so great.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.635
I do?

16:08.668 --> 16:12.139
I think you should wear that
tonight, don't you think?

16:12.172 --> 16:14.041
Maybe.

16:14.074 --> 16:16.209
I mean, only if you want
to make a good impression.

16:16.243 --> 16:20.380
I do. Are you sure
it looks good?

16:20.413 --> 16:23.683
I think you
always look good.

16:23.716 --> 16:26.553
And this is
totally up to you,

16:26.586 --> 16:30.223
but I think everything
might be just a little small.

16:30.257 --> 16:32.559
Yeah, I didn't
want to say anything.

16:32.592 --> 16:33.960
Baby, I'm so sorry.

16:33.993 --> 16:36.363
I should know your size.

16:36.396 --> 16:39.566
I'll go get the right sizes
right now.

16:39.599 --> 16:41.034
You don't have to go now.

16:41.068 --> 16:43.303
No, I want to.
Got to make a good impression.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.638
Thanks.
Plus, we need wine.

16:45.672 --> 16:49.809
Don't you need these clothes,
to exchange them?

16:49.842 --> 16:52.579
Oh, right, right.
Right.

16:52.612 --> 16:53.646
[ Door closes ]

16:53.680 --> 17:00.820
**

17:00.853 --> 17:07.994
**

17:08.027 --> 17:10.597
* It got a mind of its own
and it say *

17:10.630 --> 17:12.765
* Woke up

17:12.799 --> 17:16.869
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
* Don't recognize the bed

17:16.903 --> 17:17.937
Hi.

17:17.970 --> 17:19.272
Why do you say "hi"

17:19.306 --> 17:22.041
like you have no idea
I've called you 11 times?

17:22.075 --> 17:23.410
How do you want me to say it?

17:23.443 --> 17:24.877
Like, "Christian,
oh, my God,

17:24.911 --> 17:26.346
I'm so sorry I've
been ignoring you.

17:26.379 --> 17:28.115
You helped me so much
with stealing and breaking into

17:28.148 --> 17:30.350
Lashever's phone
so I could find Javier.

17:30.383 --> 17:33.086
But I never even called you
to let you know it worked.

17:33.120 --> 17:36.756
Thank you so much, Christian,
and I miss you."

17:36.789 --> 17:37.790
Hi.

17:37.824 --> 17:39.025
How do you know it worked?

17:39.058 --> 17:40.793
Because Lashever
came back to my place.

17:40.827 --> 17:42.962
So you did get laid.
Congrats.

17:42.995 --> 17:45.265
Yeah, and she was still
at my place the next morning

17:45.298 --> 17:47.467
when she got a text about
Javier getting away,

17:47.500 --> 17:48.935
that he escaped
the whole thing.

17:48.968 --> 17:50.970
Wow, that's good to know.

17:51.003 --> 17:52.305
Wait, you didn't know?

17:52.339 --> 17:53.606
Nope, they never found him.

17:53.640 --> 17:55.308
Then how did he get away?

17:55.342 --> 17:58.578
Excuse me, miss? Would you mind
taking your phone call outside?

17:58.611 --> 17:59.712
Store policy.

17:59.746 --> 18:01.481
Of course.
I'm so sorry.

18:01.514 --> 18:03.316
I have no idea
how he got away.

18:03.350 --> 18:06.653
I haven't talked to him,
and I have no idea where he is.

18:06.686 --> 18:07.954
So where are you?

18:07.987 --> 18:09.922
With Jacob.
We're fine.

18:09.956 --> 18:12.325
And thank you
for helping me that night.

18:12.359 --> 18:14.827
Even though I didn't
even up finding Javier,

18:14.861 --> 18:16.496
thank you for helping me try.

18:16.529 --> 18:18.631
Of course. Anytime.

18:18.665 --> 18:20.967
Great.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.136
So if you find out
that Lashever is setting

18:23.170 --> 18:25.838
another trap for Javier,
you'll let me know.

18:25.872 --> 18:27.140
You are with him.

18:27.174 --> 18:30.177
No, I'm not, but if you
stay close to her

18:30.210 --> 18:33.946
and find anything out,
I'd just really appreciate it

18:33.980 --> 18:35.615
if you keep me in the loop.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.850
I won't be seeing
much of her anymore.

18:37.884 --> 18:40.753
She's not interested
in a relationship.

18:40.787 --> 18:42.689
So?
Be fuck buddies.

18:42.722 --> 18:45.325
[ Phone clicks ]

18:45.358 --> 18:46.993
Jacob: It's cool
that this house comes with

18:47.026 --> 18:48.528
silverware and plates.

18:48.561 --> 18:51.531
Yeah, that's how it works
with vacation houses.

18:51.564 --> 18:53.866
So you don't have to buy
everything for just a few days.

18:53.900 --> 18:55.134
Can we stay forever?

18:55.168 --> 18:56.869
No. If you stay too long,

18:56.903 --> 18:59.939
vacation houses are much more
expensive than regular houses.

18:59.972 --> 19:01.274
Because of the plates.

19:01.308 --> 19:03.710
Because of the plates
and the towels

19:03.743 --> 19:06.346
and the silverware
and the coffee machine.

19:06.379 --> 19:08.548
Mom hates
that coffee machine.

19:08.581 --> 19:12.185
So do I.

19:12.219 --> 19:14.020
What if people
want coffee tonight?

19:14.053 --> 19:15.722
Should I call mom
and tell her to get

19:15.755 --> 19:19.859
a new machine
while she's out?

19:19.892 --> 19:22.395
She's not here?

19:22.429 --> 19:23.996
No.

19:24.030 --> 19:26.233
**

19:26.266 --> 19:28.067
[ Garage door opens ]

19:28.100 --> 19:31.904
**

19:31.938 --> 19:35.242
Thank you.

19:35.275 --> 19:36.676
Big party tonight?

19:36.709 --> 19:38.845
Nope, it's all for me.

19:38.878 --> 19:41.914
Wow. Nice.
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

19:41.948 --> 19:51.924
**

19:51.958 --> 20:01.934
**

20:01.968 --> 20:05.838
[ Car door beeping ]

20:05.872 --> 20:14.113
**

20:14.146 --> 20:22.455
**

20:22.489 --> 20:26.125
I forgot this was in here.

20:28.328 --> 20:31.431
My husband went hunting
this morning.

20:34.133 --> 20:36.436
And fishing.

20:36.469 --> 20:40.407
**

20:40.440 --> 20:42.975
Put the wine in the back seat.

20:43.009 --> 20:46.279
[ Beeping ]

20:51.684 --> 20:58.758
**

20:58.791 --> 21:05.832
**

21:05.865 --> 21:07.334
Hey, baby.

21:07.367 --> 21:09.802
I got everything we need
in a bigger size.

21:09.836 --> 21:11.170
Want to go change?

21:11.203 --> 21:13.072
Apple and her mom
are coming in five minutes.

21:13.105 --> 21:14.574
Well, then, you have
five minutes.

21:14.607 --> 21:17.510
Plus, I need to talk
to Javier about something.

21:17.544 --> 21:23.616
**

21:23.650 --> 21:25.518
I thought
I was hallucinating.

21:25.552 --> 21:27.119
I didn't know you
left with the car.

21:27.153 --> 21:28.688
As soon as I knew,
I called you.

21:28.721 --> 21:31.023
You brought a dead body
into this house?

21:31.057 --> 21:32.492
It's a long story.

21:32.525 --> 21:34.661
I don't want to hear
your stupid long story.

21:34.694 --> 21:37.163
Woman: Hello?!

21:37.196 --> 21:38.698
Hi.

21:38.731 --> 21:41.468
The door was open, so sorry
we're a few minutes early,

21:41.501 --> 21:43.803
but Apple and I just couldn't
wait another minute to meet you.

21:43.836 --> 21:46.639
And we couldn't wait
another minute to meet you.

21:46.673 --> 21:48.675
Oh, and thank you.

21:48.708 --> 21:50.142
You must be Apple.

21:50.176 --> 21:52.178
Michael will be down
in just a second.

21:52.211 --> 21:53.713
-Okay.
-Your son was so adorable

21:53.746 --> 21:55.615
to invite us over, but then,
I didn't know if it was

21:55.648 --> 21:57.049
really okay, but I didn't
have your number,

21:57.083 --> 21:58.317
and neither did Apple.

21:58.351 --> 22:00.820
And anyway,
I'm Carin with a "C."

22:00.853 --> 22:02.021
A what?

22:02.054 --> 22:03.690
It's Carin with a "C,"
not a "K."

22:03.723 --> 22:04.857
Oh.

22:04.891 --> 22:06.526
C-A-R-I-N.

22:06.559 --> 22:09.362
Well, I'm Lindsey,
and this is Emile.

22:09.396 --> 22:10.563
Hey.

22:10.597 --> 22:12.331
Look at Emile
in the kitchen.

22:12.365 --> 22:13.700
Look at me.

22:13.733 --> 22:15.735
Could you get the rest
of the wine, honey?

22:15.768 --> 22:17.336
Is there more wine?

22:17.370 --> 22:20.573
Three more cases
in the garage.

22:20.607 --> 22:23.543
In the car.

22:23.576 --> 22:24.711
Oh.

22:24.744 --> 22:27.246
[ Insects chirping ]

22:29.949 --> 22:33.185
What's your favorite movie?

22:33.219 --> 22:35.722
If, uh...
If I'm being honest,

22:35.755 --> 22:37.690
or if I'm just trying
to impress you?

22:37.724 --> 22:41.093
Both. You're talking
to an FBI agent.

22:41.127 --> 22:43.362
Okay, fine. Uh...

22:43.396 --> 22:45.097
"The Bodyguard."

22:45.131 --> 22:47.166
Ah, me too.

22:47.199 --> 22:48.601
No shit?

22:48.635 --> 22:50.870
People don't give
Whitney Houston enough credit

22:50.903 --> 22:52.772
for her chops in that film.

22:52.805 --> 22:55.942
I took knife-throwing classes
'cause of "The Bodyguard."

22:55.975 --> 22:57.276
[ Game beeps ]

22:57.309 --> 23:00.246
Where's my sandwich?

23:00.279 --> 23:03.816
[ Insects chirping ]

23:11.958 --> 23:16.262
[ Crunching ]

23:16.295 --> 23:20.066
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm,
mm, mm, mm.

23:20.099 --> 23:21.601
You like that?
Oh, ho!

23:21.634 --> 23:24.537
I'll take a Rob sandwich
any day.

23:24.571 --> 23:27.073
[ Laughs ]
All right.

23:27.106 --> 23:28.908
Where's your mom?

23:28.941 --> 23:30.242
My mom?

23:30.276 --> 23:31.410
Estelle.

23:31.444 --> 23:33.145
Estelle's my wife.

23:33.179 --> 23:36.916
[ Laughs ]

23:36.949 --> 23:38.718
[ Door opens, shuts ]

23:38.751 --> 23:41.153
[ Laughs ]

23:41.187 --> 23:43.255
What the hell's
happening?

23:43.289 --> 23:44.423
She's FBI.

23:44.457 --> 23:46.425
I know who she is.
You do?

23:46.459 --> 23:48.327
Why did you let her
in this house?

23:48.360 --> 23:50.062
I don't know.

23:50.096 --> 23:54.734
I don't know what this is about.
Why wouldn't I let her in?

23:54.767 --> 23:57.604
Winner.

23:57.637 --> 24:00.507
Rob, go do
something else.

24:00.540 --> 24:01.941
We're feeling things out,

24:01.974 --> 24:04.611
seeing if we like Tybee
enough to stay for good.

24:04.644 --> 24:06.846
One of the big things
is finding a school.

24:06.879 --> 24:09.782
Oh, of course. You get to play
hooky for a little while, huh?

24:09.816 --> 24:11.851
Nope, he hasn't
missed a single day.

24:11.884 --> 24:14.253
We've been
home schooling him.

24:14.286 --> 24:17.289
Oh, wow.

24:17.323 --> 24:18.925
Until we find
the right school,

24:18.958 --> 24:20.960
it's better than putting him
in the wrong one.

24:20.993 --> 24:23.262
Well, it's the middle of
the year is the hard part.

24:23.295 --> 24:25.264
Did you try
the public school?

24:25.297 --> 24:27.033
We don't have
a permanent address yet,

24:27.066 --> 24:29.468
but we want him to go
private regardless, you know.

24:29.502 --> 24:32.772
Of course.
Did you try Ravinia Academy?

24:32.805 --> 24:36.208
Yeah. Don't quote me on this,
but they were...

24:36.242 --> 24:37.610
Racist?

24:37.644 --> 24:39.045
I didn't want to say it.

24:39.078 --> 24:40.613
I've heard the rumors.

24:40.647 --> 24:43.616
At Cedarwood Country Day,
we have a very strict policy

24:43.650 --> 24:45.451
against any sort
of discrimination.

24:45.484 --> 24:47.453
Yeah, including
against gay kids.

24:47.486 --> 24:49.221
-Even though there aren't any.
-Huh.

24:49.255 --> 24:50.456
Brooke Nelson's a lesbian.

24:50.489 --> 24:51.724
Since when?

24:51.758 --> 24:52.859
Tuesday.

24:52.892 --> 24:55.127
Well, okay.

24:55.161 --> 24:56.696
[ Laughs ]

24:56.729 --> 25:01.534
Do you think Cedarwood would be
a good place for Michael?

25:01.568 --> 25:04.403
Oh, I assumed that you had
already applied there.

25:04.436 --> 25:07.740
Not yet. We hear
it's pretty exclusive.

25:07.774 --> 25:11.243
Well, it is.
I mean, it's number one.

25:11.277 --> 25:14.213
I know the wait list
is kind of long, but --

25:14.246 --> 25:15.347
But he's black.

25:15.381 --> 25:16.849
Why would you
say that, honey?

25:16.883 --> 25:18.217
Because he is.

25:18.250 --> 25:19.886
Diversity
is my campaign platform.

25:19.919 --> 25:22.021
And we only have
two black kids.

25:22.054 --> 25:23.823
Which is a real shame.

25:23.856 --> 25:29.261
Well, I bet you get
very good grades, Michael.

25:29.295 --> 25:31.998
We don't do grades
in home schooling,

25:32.031 --> 25:35.434
which is a problem because all
of the schools want his records.

25:35.467 --> 25:37.704
Oh, so you've always
home schooled him?

25:37.737 --> 25:39.906
For the last
few years, yeah.

25:39.939 --> 25:44.777
Because of Emile's career.
He was a philanthropist.

25:44.811 --> 25:48.414
Fundraising, really,
mostly for celebrities

25:48.447 --> 25:49.882
and their various causes.

25:49.916 --> 25:51.951
You've raised money
for a couple of private schools,

25:51.984 --> 25:52.952
right, honey?

25:52.985 --> 25:55.054
Yeah.
Yeah.

25:55.087 --> 25:56.455
How great is that?

25:56.488 --> 25:59.859
Well, kind of.
It was a whole whirlwind life.

25:59.892 --> 26:02.629
Emile was all over
the world 24/7,

26:02.662 --> 26:05.064
and we did our best
to keep up, but it just got

26:05.097 --> 26:09.602
harder and harder, and then
after Gwyneth Paltrow, ugh.

26:09.636 --> 26:11.804
Oh, my God,
Gwyneth Paltrow?

26:11.838 --> 26:13.640
I'm named
after her daughter.

26:13.673 --> 26:15.908
No, you're not.

26:15.942 --> 26:18.277
So you can tell Emile is
a pretty good cook, right?

26:18.310 --> 26:21.147
Mm, yeah. I can't get
my chicken to taste like this.

26:21.180 --> 26:24.150
Well, so, he was working on
Gwyneth's charities

26:24.183 --> 26:26.418
for over a year
when she started having him

26:26.452 --> 26:27.954
cook for her
dinner parties, too.

26:27.987 --> 26:29.121
No way.

26:29.155 --> 26:30.957
But wait, you know
her website, Goop?

26:30.990 --> 26:32.258
Yeah.

26:32.291 --> 26:35.427
Pretty soon, Emile started
seeing his recipes on there.

26:35.461 --> 26:38.297
She didn't ask.
She didn't pay for them.

26:38.330 --> 26:42.669
She just stole them,
put 'em in her cookbook, too.

26:42.702 --> 26:45.972
I have that cookbook.

26:46.005 --> 26:48.174
Then you have
stolen recipes.

26:48.207 --> 26:50.076
Unbelievable.

26:50.109 --> 26:52.645
Who does that?

26:52.679 --> 26:55.614
Gwyneth Paltrow.

26:55.648 --> 26:57.950
So we just decided,
you know what?

26:57.984 --> 27:02.588
Let's try to live a simple,
more normal life,

27:02.621 --> 27:04.857
and that's what
we're trying to do.

27:08.294 --> 27:09.962
That is so cool.

27:09.996 --> 27:13.099
Cheers to that.

27:13.132 --> 27:14.533
Cheers to that.

27:14.566 --> 27:17.336
[ Glasses clink ]

27:17.369 --> 27:24.010
**

27:29.315 --> 27:30.382
Are we done?

27:30.416 --> 27:33.485
Mm, yes, thank you.

27:33.519 --> 27:35.788
I mean, are we done?

27:35.822 --> 27:38.057
I have no information
for you.

27:38.090 --> 27:39.992
Can you leave?

27:40.026 --> 27:41.660
Without dessert?

27:41.694 --> 27:45.531
J.K.
I'm off sugar.

27:45.564 --> 27:49.535
But I really do need
to find your daughter.

27:49.568 --> 27:51.537
But I can't help you
with that.

27:51.570 --> 27:54.306
I've told you,
I don't know where she is.

27:54.340 --> 27:55.975
I find that
hard to believe.

27:56.008 --> 27:59.045
Really? Does your mother
know where you are all the time?

27:59.078 --> 28:00.546
Of course she does.

28:00.579 --> 28:02.648
Your daughter? Letty?

28:02.681 --> 28:04.050
Yeah, I'm aware
of her name.

28:04.083 --> 28:06.719
Your daughter Letty
got her son back because

28:06.753 --> 28:09.055
she agreed to help me
with a thing.

28:09.088 --> 28:12.691
Only that thing
didn't go so well.

28:12.725 --> 28:15.862
Did she do whatever you
asked her to do?

28:15.895 --> 28:17.063
She did.

28:17.096 --> 28:19.999
Oh, well, then she doesn't
owe you anything.

28:20.032 --> 28:22.869
The last thing Letty needs
is to get pulled back

28:22.902 --> 28:25.872
into any more shit
with drug dealers.

28:25.905 --> 28:28.707
Thank you for
clearing her record.

28:28.741 --> 28:32.444
Thank you for helping her
get custody of Jacob.

28:32.478 --> 28:34.847
And I'll thank you
for leaving my house.

28:34.881 --> 28:36.515
Okay.

28:36.548 --> 28:38.885
Okay.

28:38.918 --> 28:44.723
Well, if you do
find out where she is,

28:44.757 --> 28:49.595
and you feel like
letting me know, here is my...

28:49.628 --> 28:51.197
[ Rustling ]

28:51.230 --> 28:53.800
...card.

28:53.833 --> 28:57.069
[ Clunking ]
Somewhere.

29:00.840 --> 29:02.809
I wouldn't know
the first thing about

29:02.842 --> 29:04.143
how to home school Apple.

29:04.176 --> 29:05.444
I'd be the worst.

29:05.477 --> 29:06.779
She'd be
home schooling me.

29:06.813 --> 29:08.280
Letty: Well, that's
kind of how it is.

29:08.314 --> 29:11.450
I mean, how am I supposed
to remember hypotenuses

29:11.483 --> 29:12.618
or whatever?

29:12.651 --> 29:14.453
I can't even balance
my checkbook.

29:14.486 --> 29:16.422
You still have a checkbook?

29:16.455 --> 29:19.158
Mm.

29:19.191 --> 29:21.060
[ Sighs ]

29:21.093 --> 29:24.096
Jacob really is
brilliant, though.

29:24.130 --> 29:26.132
He's much smarter than me.

29:26.165 --> 29:31.437
He's perceptive
and kind and curious.

29:31.470 --> 29:33.940
He could be anything.

29:33.973 --> 29:37.944
I just want
the best for him.

29:37.977 --> 29:41.113
Who's Jacob?

29:41.147 --> 29:42.748
Michael, Michael.

29:42.781 --> 29:44.450
Jacob is his middle name.

29:44.483 --> 29:48.354
Oh, okay.
[ Chuckles ]

29:48.387 --> 29:50.122
[ Line ringing ]

29:50.156 --> 29:52.524
Cheers.

29:52.558 --> 29:57.830
**

29:57.864 --> 30:02.969
[ Ringing continues ]

30:03.002 --> 30:04.670
Female voice:
Your call has been forwarded

30:04.703 --> 30:06.839
to an automated
voice messaging system.

30:06.873 --> 30:10.009
Silk: Silk...
Female voice: ...is not --

30:10.042 --> 30:12.644
I don't think you can play
this game with just two people.

30:12.678 --> 30:17.283
Who cares about the rules?

30:17.316 --> 30:21.020
Maybe she's born with it.
Maybe it's blank.

30:22.821 --> 30:24.823
A lifetime of sadness?

30:24.857 --> 30:26.092
Yeah.

30:29.228 --> 30:32.331
With enough time and pressure,
blank will turn into blank.

30:32.364 --> 30:34.033
Home schooling
sounds weird.

30:34.066 --> 30:36.168
You need to get out of it,
I mean,

30:36.202 --> 30:38.170
if you ever
want to have sex.

30:38.204 --> 30:39.171
I'm trying.

30:39.205 --> 30:41.373
I know.
I think it's working.

30:41.407 --> 30:44.010
It was smart of your mom
to talk about Gwyneth Paltrow.

30:44.043 --> 30:46.578
She's smart
about stuff like that.

30:46.612 --> 30:48.580
Who are your real
mom and dad?

30:48.614 --> 30:51.017
You mean, who are
the black people?

30:51.050 --> 30:52.684
Yeah.

30:52.718 --> 30:54.853
My dad is black.
He lives in Myrtle Beach.

30:54.887 --> 30:57.856
My mom is downstairs.
She's my real mom.

30:57.890 --> 30:59.191
With enough time
and pressure --

30:59.225 --> 31:00.692
Why are hair products
for black people

31:00.726 --> 31:02.194
always in
a separate section?

31:02.228 --> 31:04.530
I think it just makes it
easier for black people.

31:04.563 --> 31:07.699
Oh. Also then white people
would accidentally use

31:07.733 --> 31:09.368
black people stuff
and keep returning it

31:09.401 --> 31:10.869
and complaining.

31:10.903 --> 31:12.104
Yeah.

31:12.138 --> 31:14.373
With enough time and pressure,
blank turns into blank.

31:14.406 --> 31:17.543
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Carin:
No, Eric, I'm having fun.

31:17.576 --> 31:18.844
Letty: [ Chuckles ]

31:18.877 --> 31:19.711
Bye.

31:19.745 --> 31:23.382
[ Both laugh ]

31:23.415 --> 31:24.550
[ Sighs ]

31:24.583 --> 31:26.552
Eric would never
do the dishes.

31:26.585 --> 31:28.020
Oh, just make him do them.

31:28.054 --> 31:33.125
It's too late now.
He won't change.

31:33.159 --> 31:36.929
Do you know how happy I am
to have you and Emile here?

31:36.963 --> 31:40.566
To have people living
across the street who are real,

31:40.599 --> 31:42.234
who don't judge?

31:42.268 --> 31:44.971
Most of my friends here,
if they saw me smoking,

31:45.004 --> 31:46.973
they would not
know what to do.

31:47.006 --> 31:48.807
They're doing other things.

31:48.840 --> 31:50.742
They most definitely are.

31:50.776 --> 31:53.212
Oh, my God.

31:53.245 --> 31:54.480
You can't move
somewhere else.

31:54.513 --> 31:55.914
I know.

31:55.948 --> 31:58.217
I feel like you and me
would have so much fun.

31:58.250 --> 31:59.551
I know, I know.

31:59.585 --> 32:01.988
I mean, I'd love that,

32:02.021 --> 32:04.223
but we have to find
the right school for Michael.

32:04.256 --> 32:07.093
Well, I am gonna
make it happen, then.

32:07.126 --> 32:08.760
That's that.

32:08.794 --> 32:11.097
Y--
It won't be easy,

32:11.130 --> 32:13.799
but Emile's experience with
fundraising will be a big plus.

32:13.832 --> 32:15.167
I know all the people.

32:15.201 --> 32:17.103
I'll make all the right
phone calls.

32:17.136 --> 32:18.004
Really?

32:18.037 --> 32:19.305
I'm gonna
send e-mails, too.

32:19.338 --> 32:23.109
Wow, that's --
that's amazing. Thank you.

32:23.142 --> 32:26.612
We are gonna get him
into that school

32:26.645 --> 32:28.614
because we need
to be friends.

32:28.647 --> 32:30.016
[ Glasses clink ]

32:30.049 --> 32:32.151
Cheers.
Cheers.

32:32.184 --> 32:33.986
Eric: Apple!

32:34.020 --> 32:35.287
Apple!

32:35.321 --> 32:36.688
-Eric?
-I tracked the location

32:36.722 --> 32:37.956
of my daughter's phone.

32:37.990 --> 32:39.358
She is in this house.
Where is she?

32:39.391 --> 32:40.926
-Sir, please calm down.
-Is he your husband?

32:40.959 --> 32:42.661
Don't tell me to calm down.
Apple!

32:42.694 --> 32:44.463
What in God's name --

32:44.496 --> 32:46.165
Eric, calm down.

32:46.198 --> 32:48.434
Apple and I just came over
here for dinner.

32:48.467 --> 32:50.836
I thought you weren't gonna
be home until later.

32:50.869 --> 32:55.007
[ Footsteps approaching ]

32:55.041 --> 32:57.309
-Is this a joke?
-We're being friendly.

32:57.343 --> 32:59.278
Carin:
Apple wants her new friend
to go to Cedarwood.

32:59.311 --> 33:02.281
Oh, let me guess.
You told them you could help.

33:02.314 --> 33:06.818
Let's go, honey.

33:06.852 --> 33:08.887
Uh...

33:12.491 --> 33:13.792
Sorry.

33:13.825 --> 33:17.863
He is --

33:17.896 --> 33:20.799
I'm sorry.

33:20.832 --> 33:28.340
**

33:28.374 --> 33:30.142
You tried.

33:30.176 --> 33:31.843
No shit.

33:31.877 --> 33:34.846
And you're trying
to ruin my life.

33:34.880 --> 33:37.116
Get out here!

33:41.287 --> 33:43.055
Who the hell do you
think you are?

33:43.089 --> 33:46.592
It was self-defense.
You're the worst liar.

33:46.625 --> 33:49.395
Fine, but I'm not lying,
and you are drunk.

33:49.428 --> 33:51.730
So what?
I could drink all four cases

33:51.763 --> 33:53.565
of that wine,
and it wouldn't come close

33:53.599 --> 33:56.435
to you killing someone and
putting the body in the garage.

33:56.468 --> 33:58.036
Do you realize
what would have happened

33:58.070 --> 33:59.271
if that cop had seen?

33:59.305 --> 34:01.006
If Jacob and his friend
had decided

34:01.039 --> 34:02.241
to come in here and play?

34:02.274 --> 34:04.110
I understand.
No, you don't.

34:04.143 --> 34:05.277
You don't!

34:05.311 --> 34:06.612
I finally have Jacob.

34:06.645 --> 34:08.447
I have
a totally clean record,

34:08.480 --> 34:11.250
and all of that would have
been gone in about one second.

34:11.283 --> 34:13.185
Do you really think
that my plan would be

34:13.219 --> 34:14.553
to kill someone
and drive the body here?

34:14.586 --> 34:16.955
That's exactly
what you did.

34:16.988 --> 34:18.524
I thought it was just
a normal job.

34:18.557 --> 34:20.692
So you were going
to kill someone?

34:20.726 --> 34:21.960
I --

34:21.993 --> 34:23.295
Yes.

34:23.329 --> 34:24.963
You realize how stupid
that is, right?

34:24.996 --> 34:28.134
Any job you take could be
the FBI setting you up again.

34:28.167 --> 34:29.568
I took this job before that,

34:29.601 --> 34:31.303
before you sold me out
to the FBI.

34:31.337 --> 34:32.638
And it was a trap.

34:32.671 --> 34:34.640
He was another hit man
there to kill me.

34:34.673 --> 34:37.909
Why? Who wants you dead?
Besides me?

34:37.943 --> 34:40.412
I don't know.
Well, who hired you?

34:40.446 --> 34:43.115
I don't know. A guy.
I met him at a bar.

34:43.149 --> 34:44.950
He gave me an envelope.
Told me a story.

34:44.983 --> 34:47.319
I'm not gonna call him just
to let him know how alive I am.

34:47.353 --> 34:49.655
You're not supposed
to be doing this anymore.

34:49.688 --> 34:50.989
Oh, really?

34:51.022 --> 34:57.463
Just like you're not supposed
to be stealing anymore, huh?

34:57.496 --> 35:00.799
That is all the stuff
I'm hiding for Christmas.

35:00.832 --> 35:02.901
[ Laughs ]

35:02.934 --> 35:04.069
Right,
all presents for you.

35:04.102 --> 35:05.737
At least I'm trying.

35:05.771 --> 35:06.772
What?

35:06.805 --> 35:08.307
I'm making an effort.

35:08.340 --> 35:09.908
Yeah, but you're
still stealing things.

35:09.941 --> 35:11.343
In dark moments.

35:11.377 --> 35:14.313
But you -- you never
even tried not to kill.

35:14.346 --> 35:15.681
I tried not to steal.

35:15.714 --> 35:17.683
Well, then, that's
what happened to me.

35:17.716 --> 35:18.684
What?

35:18.717 --> 35:20.686
The dark moments thing.

35:20.719 --> 35:22.020
Oh, my God.

35:22.053 --> 35:23.355
You got a job.

35:23.389 --> 35:25.757
Yes, for you, for Jacob,
for looking normal.

35:25.791 --> 35:28.026
But do you realize
how much money we need

35:28.059 --> 35:29.428
just to pay for this house?

35:29.461 --> 35:30.829
Huh?
For private school?

35:30.862 --> 35:32.798
Where do you think
this money will come from?

35:32.831 --> 35:34.300
Not from killing people.

35:34.333 --> 35:36.702
Well, it pays well.
A lot better than a line cook,

35:36.735 --> 35:38.704
and I had already
accepted the money.

35:38.737 --> 35:40.206
Do you know what happens
if I take the money,

35:40.239 --> 35:41.840
but then don't do the job?

35:41.873 --> 35:43.041
[ Ring tone playing ]

35:43.074 --> 35:45.777
What was that?

35:45.811 --> 35:47.613
I don't know.

35:47.646 --> 35:50.549
That was a phone.
Whose phone was that?

35:50.582 --> 35:53.652
-It's probably mine.
-That's not your phone.

35:53.685 --> 35:55.554
That ring tone
is super annoying.

35:55.587 --> 35:57.122
I would never be with you
in the first place

35:57.155 --> 35:58.957
if that was the sound
your phone made.

35:58.990 --> 36:00.559
That's his phone.

36:00.592 --> 36:01.660
Pull it out.

36:01.693 --> 36:02.894
You pull it out.

36:02.928 --> 36:04.129
I'm not touching
that body.

36:04.162 --> 36:05.897
You are the one
who wants the phone.

36:05.931 --> 36:08.066
If he tried to kill you, don't
you want to know who he is?

36:08.099 --> 36:09.235
So now you believe me?

36:09.268 --> 36:11.069
I am trying to help you.

36:11.102 --> 36:12.638
I don't care who he is.

36:12.671 --> 36:15.006
He's a hit man. And it
won't be his real phone.

36:15.040 --> 36:16.041
It'll be a burner.

36:16.074 --> 36:18.244
Pull it out.

36:18.277 --> 36:21.247
[ Sighs ]

36:21.280 --> 36:26.218
**

36:26.252 --> 36:29.087
[ Beeping ]

36:29.120 --> 36:35.093
**

36:35.126 --> 36:41.166
**

36:41.199 --> 36:43.702
Use his thumb.

36:43.735 --> 36:53.078
**

36:53.111 --> 36:56.315
JP. That's me.

36:59.084 --> 37:01.687
Text back "It's done,"

37:01.720 --> 37:06.124
so they definitely think
you're dead.

37:06.157 --> 37:08.627
[ Cellphone keys clicking ]

37:08.660 --> 37:12.564
**

37:12.598 --> 37:15.401
Look how sad you would be.

37:15.434 --> 37:17.603
That's not
what I was thinking.

37:17.636 --> 37:18.637
Okay.

37:18.670 --> 37:21.139
What are you going to do
with this body?

37:21.172 --> 37:23.809
I don't know yet.

37:23.842 --> 37:26.278
Well, what was
your original plan?

37:26.312 --> 37:27.546
I was going to give him
a heart attack.

37:27.579 --> 37:28.880
I was going to
leave him there.

37:28.914 --> 37:30.649
Ugh, always with
the heart attack thing.

37:30.682 --> 37:32.984
You need to get
more creative.

37:33.018 --> 37:34.486
I used to be creative.

37:34.520 --> 37:36.555
The heart attack is
the best way every time.

37:36.588 --> 37:38.657
Not every time, obviously.

37:38.690 --> 37:41.560
And why is it always a boring
sport like fishing or golf?

37:41.593 --> 37:43.995
It is not always that.
I'm just doing what they do.

37:44.029 --> 37:48.334
I kill a lot of white men.

37:48.367 --> 37:50.168
I'll figure something out.

37:50.201 --> 37:51.337
Take it to
what's his name.

37:51.370 --> 37:53.305
Silk. The funeral home.
Burn it.

37:53.339 --> 37:54.473
I can't.

37:54.506 --> 37:55.974
Why?
That's your whole thing.

37:56.007 --> 37:58.310
Silk doesn't want anything
to do with me after my father --

37:58.344 --> 38:01.012
after the dinner
with my family,

38:01.046 --> 38:04.683
which I understand.

38:04.716 --> 38:06.852
Maybe I will find
a new funeral home.

38:06.885 --> 38:09.988
What? Finding a new crematorium
and a person to trust?

38:10.021 --> 38:11.156
How long does that take?

38:11.189 --> 38:12.691
A long time.

38:12.724 --> 38:15.494
Well, it only takes two hours
to drive to Charleston.

38:15.527 --> 38:17.429
Silk can't so no
if you just show up.

38:17.463 --> 38:19.030
It's obviously
an emergency.

38:19.064 --> 38:20.699
It's always an emergency.

38:20.732 --> 38:24.970
Get in the car, drive away,
and get rid of this body.

38:25.003 --> 38:27.506
Now.

38:32.478 --> 38:33.812
[ Knock on door ]

38:33.845 --> 38:35.213
Coming.

38:35.246 --> 38:36.448
[ Knocking continues ]
I'm coming.

38:36.482 --> 38:39.050
Jesus. I'm coming.

38:42.921 --> 38:44.390
Uhh...

38:44.423 --> 38:46.124
You have a warrant?

38:46.157 --> 38:48.293
Always.

38:48.326 --> 38:50.562
But we're working
and sleeping together.

38:50.596 --> 38:51.997
Well, I thought you --

38:52.030 --> 38:55.000
Did you just say that
we're working together?

38:55.033 --> 38:56.402
You didn't realize that?

38:56.435 --> 38:58.370
It's called servitude.

38:58.404 --> 39:00.406
It's called
you're a henchman.

39:00.439 --> 39:02.140
And you're already
failing miserably.

39:02.173 --> 39:03.575
How could I --

39:03.609 --> 39:05.677
Letty is with Javier.
No, she's not.

39:05.711 --> 39:07.178
Oh, so
you've talked to her?

39:07.212 --> 39:09.415
No, no.
Did you?

39:09.448 --> 39:10.816
I talked to her mother.
Estelle.

39:10.849 --> 39:11.983
When?

39:12.017 --> 39:13.819
She thinks her daughter
ratted out a drug dealer,

39:13.852 --> 39:17.188
which means Letty never
told her who Javier really is.

39:17.222 --> 39:18.323
Why would she?

39:18.356 --> 39:19.758
Why would she lie?

39:19.791 --> 39:22.428
I can think
of several reasons.

39:22.461 --> 39:24.696
She's still sleeping with him,
that's the reason.

39:24.730 --> 39:26.665
I'm not sure
that's the reason.

39:26.698 --> 39:29.034
This is why you're
not the FBI agent.

39:29.067 --> 39:31.603
This is why I'm the FBI agent
you work for.

39:31.637 --> 39:34.272
This is why you will
do whatever I say because

39:34.305 --> 39:35.774
we're gonna find this guy,

39:35.807 --> 39:38.009
and he's not gonna
get away this time.

39:38.043 --> 39:41.747
This is important to me,
so it's important to you.

39:41.780 --> 39:43.114
Comprende?

39:43.148 --> 39:44.416
Yes.

39:44.450 --> 39:46.885
That's Spanish for
"Do you understand?"

39:46.918 --> 39:49.120
I know.

39:49.154 --> 39:51.757
Because he's Spanish.

39:51.790 --> 39:55.060
I think he's
Argentinian, but...

39:55.093 --> 39:56.662
Get help.

39:58.930 --> 40:03.469
-Did you call Letty?
-Nope.

40:03.502 --> 40:06.204
Don't you want to know
where she is, at least?

40:06.237 --> 40:10.108
Yeah, I do.

40:10.141 --> 40:12.110
But then I'd know.

40:12.143 --> 40:14.412
And...

40:14.446 --> 40:18.249
then I'd have to tell.

40:18.283 --> 40:20.852
And nothing good
will happen.

40:23.354 --> 40:29.160
Yeah, well, if nothing good
will happen, then screw it.

40:29.194 --> 40:36.001
**

40:36.034 --> 40:42.908
**

40:42.941 --> 40:46.812
[ Lock clicking ]

40:46.845 --> 40:49.648
[ Knocks on door ]
Jacob?

40:49.681 --> 40:53.485
-Yeah?
-Can I come in?

40:55.386 --> 40:58.657
[ Door opens ]

40:58.690 --> 41:00.492
Why did you have
the door locked?

41:00.526 --> 41:03.194
For privacy.

41:07.799 --> 41:12.370
Look, I know you're upset,
and I totally get that.

41:12.403 --> 41:14.606
Apple's dad was
kind of crazy.

41:14.640 --> 41:16.174
It sucks about her school.

41:16.207 --> 41:19.210
But if there's an emergency,
I might have to come get you,

41:19.244 --> 41:20.979
so you can't lock the door.

41:21.012 --> 41:22.648
An emergency?

41:22.681 --> 41:25.851
Yeah, like, you know,
you might be sleeping,

41:25.884 --> 41:28.353
and there's a fire
in the kitchen or something.

41:28.386 --> 41:30.556
Because you got drunk.
What?

41:30.589 --> 41:32.190
I'm just saying,
maybe one day you'll

41:32.223 --> 41:33.892
start a fire in the kitchen
because you drank too much.

41:33.925 --> 41:35.393
That's not
what this is about.

41:35.426 --> 41:37.663
This is about
not locking the door.

41:37.696 --> 41:39.798
Can you knock next time?
I did knock.

41:39.831 --> 41:41.132
After you tried to come in.

41:41.166 --> 41:44.502
I -- If that's what
I did, I'm sorry.

41:44.536 --> 41:46.004
I just don't want
people barging in.

41:46.037 --> 41:47.072
People?

41:47.105 --> 41:49.474
Who else would it be
besides me or Javier?

41:49.507 --> 41:50.909
I don't know.
I don't want anyone to come

41:50.942 --> 41:54.079
take me away from you
like they did last time.

41:54.112 --> 41:56.915
No -- nobody is
taking you anywhere.

41:56.948 --> 41:59.350
You're safe,
do you hear me?

41:59.384 --> 42:03.088
You're safe.

42:03.121 --> 42:05.423
[ Sobs ]

42:05.456 --> 42:07.893
We will get you
a new school.

42:07.926 --> 42:09.160
Somewhere.

42:09.194 --> 42:12.330
How do you know?

42:12.363 --> 42:14.099
I don't know,

42:14.132 --> 42:17.035
but we will.

42:17.068 --> 42:19.605
But only if you leave
the door unlocked.

42:19.638 --> 42:22.574
Only if you knock first.

42:22.608 --> 42:25.043
I will.

42:25.076 --> 42:29.781
**

